"v. 喷出；滔滔不绝地讲 【英】 v.喷出(to eject in a stream)；滔滔不绝地讲(to speak readily) 【记】 和spouse(配偶)一起 记 【例】 The elephant spouted water from its trunk. v. 喷出(液体、吐沫等); 滔滔不绝地讲 【记】sp = spill(v 溢出), out－喷出 【记】spray 喷雾, 喷射, 喷溅 + out；s 音：水 + p 音：喷，爆 + out 喷出→喷出，爆发出 【相关】spurt (液体等的)喷射, 喷出，squirt 喷出，sprout 萌芽 spout (v.)  ""to issue forcible, as a liquid,"" early 14c., related to Middle Dutch spoiten ""to spout"" (Dutch spuiten ""to flow, spout""), North Frisian spütji ""spout, squirt,"" Swedish sputa ""to spout,"" from Proto-Germanic *sput-, from PIE *sp(y)eu- ""to spew, spit"" (see spew (v.)). Meaning ""to talk, declaim"" is recorded from 1610s. Related: Spouted; spouting. spout (n.)  late 14c., from spout (v.). Cognate with Middle Dutch spoit, North Frisian spütj. It was the slang term for the lift in a pawnbroker's shop, the device which took up articles for storage, hence figurative phrase up the spout ""lost, hopeless, gone beyond recall"" (1812)."
